Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Bring a large #saucepan of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the linguine.

Pop the @skin-on British chicken breasts{2} into a large #bowl and season with the @dried rosemary{1%tsp}, salt and @ground black pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, lay the chicken into the frying pan, skin-side down. Fry until the skin is golden, ~{5-6%minutes}, then turn and cook for ~{1%minute} on the other side.

Transfer the chicken to a #baking tray, skin-side up, then roast on the top shelf of your oven until cooked through, ~{18-25%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, wipe out the (now empty) frying pan.

Halve any large broccoli stems lengthways, then cut into thirds widthways.

When your pan of water is boiling, add the @linguine{180%g} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

For the last ~{4%minutes}, add the @Tenderstem® broccoli{80%g} to the same saucepan and cook for the remaining time until tender.

Once cooked, drain everything in a #colander and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop the pasta sticking together.

When everything's almost ready, pop the #frying pan on medium-high heat with the @creme fraiche{75%g}, @chicken stock paste{10g}, @fresh pesto{50%g} and @water{100%ml} for the sauce.

Stir together until combined, then add the cooked pasta, broccoli and half the @Parmigiano Reggiano{20%g}.

Continue to stir until piping hot, add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

When the chicken is cooked, cut widthways into 6 slices.

Share your ultimate creamy pesto linguine between your bowls. Top with the chicken and a sprinkle of the remaining Parmigiano Reggiano.

Enjoy!